data.title: The Marriage of Princess Maud of Wales to Prince Christian of Denmark, 22 July 1896
data.meta_description: Photogravure of the marriage of Maud, Queen of Norway and Princess of Wales, and Haakon VII, King of Norway. Scene of the wedding held in Buckingham Palace, with the future King and Queen of Norway at the centre, with the Princess Royal kneeling before Queen Victoria and surrounded by guests. A print and an accompanying key identifying sitters, see RCIN 630802.a and RCIN 630802.b. For other impressions see RCIN 630631.1, RCIN 630631.2, RCIN 630631.3, RCIN 630631.4, RCIN 630631.5,...
